      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Early morning: The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust and will soften later than the day before. In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface. <br/> <br/> In the course of the day the natural activity of avalanches will gradually increase. <br/> In particular in starting zones where no previous releases have taken place and on very steep shady slopes more small and medium-sized natural wet avalanches are possible. <br/> The conditions are generally favourable for ski touring. Backcountry tours and ascents to alpine cabins should be concluded timely. <br/> The near-surface layers of the snowpack can be released in isolated cases by winter sport participants in particular in extremely steep terrain.",
