      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "In the last two days the wind was moderate at times especially along the border with France. <br/> The weather conditions gave rise to rapid settling of the snowpack. <br/> This situation gave rise to moistening of the snowpack below approximately 2500 m. <br/> The amount of snow is subject to significant local variations. <br/> In particular below the tree line hardly any snow is lying on southeast and southwest facing slopes. <br/> Especially at high altitudes and in high Alpine regions there is still a very large amount of snow. <br/> Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on steep shady slopes."
      },
